President Uhuru Kenyatta on Monday conducted an impromptu inspection of the construction progress of the Mombasa-Nairobi standard gauge railway.The President overflew the railway line, stopping at the Mtito Andei passenger station and the Konza signal station.President Kenyatta said the project is firmly on track and will be completed on time and on budget in June next year.At Mtito Andei, President Kenyatta addressed residents and workers, thanking them for the efforts their help in getting the rail project delivered on time. email print email print Ms Tutui said the court would have given orders for immediate realisation of the rule. But the passport was not stamped, meaning he did not pass through the immigration desk.